cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "The Orthogonality Fallacy: Iterative Co-Design as a First-Class Principle for Efficient AI"
abstract: "This repository contains the implementation for iterative co-design of algorithmic optimization (sparsity) and hardware optimization (memory layout). We demonstrate that these optimizations must be co-designed iteratively rather than sequentially for optimal performance, challenging the prevalent 'Orthogonality Fallacy' in the field."
