  journal: "Conference on Machine Learning and Systems (MLSys)"
  year: 2025
  abstract: "The prevailing paradigm for designing efficient neural networks rests on the 'Orthogonality Fallacy': the implicit assumption that algorithmic optimizations (e.g., sparsity) and hardware-level optimizations (e.g., memory layout) are separable problems. This paper dismantles this fallacy, first by providing a formal justification for the necessity of co-design through a minimal theoretical model, then by introducing a concrete framework to operationalize it." 
